    Verse: 7
Tags:
  - Power
---
Power may be justly compared to a great river; while kept within its bounds
it is both beautiful and useful; but when it overflows its banks, it is too
impetuous to be stemmed; it bears down all before it, and brings
destruction and desolation wherever it comes.
